summary: Theory based on Disney’s upcoming movie releases
body:
Theory based on Disney’s upcoming movie releases

The Disney movies are staggered in Spring- Aladdin, Lion King, and Toy Story. (Too late for Frozen teasers)

Toy Story teasers dropped 8 months before its release date- with Ralph Breaks the Internet.

The next up on the block is Dumbo (March 29th)

And Captain Marvel (March 8th)

I’m assuming, at this point, Dumbo is a focal point for Frozen teasers.

blog.name: thefeministherald
blog.title: The Feminist Herald
blog.description: Brief Feminist Updates.  Feminism: Supporting the fight against the oppression of women through activism and the interrogation of the tools used to create and perpetuate a social system that oppresses women in order to afford privilege to men, especially white men. Tools like misogynistic narratives, ideas and attitudes and their use in politics, the media, education and all other social institutions and constructs. In addition, examining and pointing out how racism, homophobia and other oppressive systems and forms of discrimination intersect with misogynistic ideas creating hybrid attitudes, narratives and ideas against women of color, LGBT women, women with disabilities and other women who face those forms of discrimination.

summary: Captain Marvel Is Crash Landing Into Disney's California Adventure Park
body:
Captain Marvel Is Crash Landing Into Disney’s California Adventure Park

We’re all eagerly waiting for Carol Danvers (Brie Larson) to make her big screen debut in Captain Marvel, but it looks like folks wanting to meet her before then can head to Anaheim for a little one-on-one with the legendary hero.

Disney Parks has announced that Captain Marvel will be heading to Disneyland Resort’s California Adventure Park, joining other heroes like Captain America, Black Panther, and Spider-Man. I’ve been psyched to see what her costume looks like up close, so this sounds totally awesome. Unless they made her do some silly song and dance show, like they’ve done for the Guardians of the Galaxy. Let’s avoid that for Captain Marvel, shall we? She’s a bit more dignified.

summary: Spring crocus lilac and sweet pea
question: Spring crocus lilac and sweet pea
answer:
Describe your favorite childhood memory: It’s gotta be a tie between the day I became Shazam, and the day @aiden-ros adopted me. I definitely wasn’t expecting either thing to happen, but I’m really happy they did! I couldn’t imagine my life without being Shazam, and I don’t know where I’d be without Mom!

Describe your first relationship or first love: I’m 8…… So I haven’t really had a first love yet?

Describe a difficult goodbye you had to make to a friend or loved one: Um……. My…. My birth parents……… I had to say good bye to them when I was really young. Some… Sometimes it still really hurts.

summary: I don't like the fact that Captain Marvel has attracted both extremes because all criticisms I find out it have a valid points...
question: I don't like the fact that Captain Marvel has attracted both extremes because all criticisms I find out it have a valid points that are then lost to angry politics. I'm not excited for the movie because Brie Larson seems to be very wooden, people have defended it by saying it's a stoic character but there are ways to be stoic while still having lively acting, Larson fails at this. I've seen other people point this out but it's always sandwiched between politics so I lose faith in their argument.
